=============================================

In this section, we will cover how to use the `docker` command to run a container. We will go over the basic syntax of the command and some advanced options that you can use to customize your container's behavior.

Basic Syntax
-------------

The basic syntax of the `docker run` command is as follows:
```
docker run [OPTIONS] IMAGE [COMMAND]
```
Here's a breakdown of each part of the syntax:

* `docker run`: This is the command that starts a new container.
